Class HttpResponseContentPerformanceData

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.HttpResponseContentPerformanceData

  • public class HttpResponseContentPerformanceData
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains performance data about the receiving of all data segments of the HTTP response content.

      • addReceiveSegmentInfo

        public void addReceiveSegmentInfo(long absoluteNanoTime,
                         long deltaNanoTime,
                         int segentSize,
                         boolean isChunkIdentifierData)
        Add performance data about the receiving of one data segement.
        Parameters:
        absoluteNanoTime - the OS time in nanoseconds when the read-operation of the data segment was started (see also java.lang.System.nanoTime())
        deltaNanoTime - delta nano time of the read-operation, used to wait for new data and to read the received data segment
        segentSize - the size of the received data segment in bytes
        isChunkIdentifierData - specifies if the data segment contains "chunk identifier data" (true), or if the data segment contains "user data" (false) such as HTML, image or video data. See RFC 2616 for further details; section 3.6.1 in particular.
